Four counties from Rift Valley have partnered with the Kenya Commercial Bank Foundation to boost development, end cattle rustling, and attract investors. Laikipia, Baringo, Isiolo, and Samburu counties have signed an agreement with the foundation, which will see it fund several projects under the Amaiya Initiative, including water provision and infrastructure. ALSO READ:

Mid air crashes threaten paragliding sport in Elgeyo Marakwet